{
  "text": "The incidence of HRS, defined as worsening of serum creatinine to levels above 1.5 mg/dL within 2 weeks for type 1 HRS and over several months for type 2 HRS, is not well established but can occur in up to 40% of cirrhotic patients [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "13182174"
